"10:70:10" : {s: 10, a: 70, w: 10, r: "شدد", t: "ٱلشَّدِيدَ", l: "شَدِيد", lc: 56, tl: "l-shadīda", lb: "কড়া",e: "the severe", b: "কঠিন", i: "keras/berat", f: 1, rm: "to bind tightly, strap, strengthen firmly, run, establish, make firm, hard, strong, be advanced (day), be intense. ushdud - harden, strengthen. shadiid (pl. shidaad & ashiddau - great, firm, strict, vehement, strong, violent, severe, mighty, terrible, stern, grievous, miserly, niggardly. (adj. of the forms faiil and fiaal are used indifferently for both m. and f.): ashuddun: age of full strength, maturity. ishtadda (vb. 8) - to act with violence, become hard."},
"10:70:11" : {s: 10, a: 70, w: 11, r: "", t: "بِمَا", l: "مَا", lc: 2557, tl: "bima", lb: "না, যা, কী/কীসে?",e: "because", b: "ওই বিষয়ে যা", i: "dengan apa/disebabkan", f: 296, rm: ""},
